That we have to go through it all again.

996
01:51:57,510 --> 01:52:02,680
Don't worry about it.
All we have left are two meals a day.

997
01:52:04,250 --> 01:52:09,420
Do you wear the scarf because it's pretty
or to cover your wrinkly neck?

998
01:52:11,650 --> 01:52:13,620
How did things go for you?

999
01:52:15,180 --> 01:52:20,990
All I thought about was her.
- What? No love affairs? No adventures?

1000
01:52:21,360 --> 01:52:22,650
Nothing at all?

1001
01:52:24,030 --> 01:52:29,650
And you? - At first lots.
Then fewer and now even fewer.

1002
01:52:31,360 --> 01:52:34,190
You know I think fate betrayed me.

1003
01:52:34,960 --> 01:52:39,020
Oh well it used to be the Führer.
Now it's fate.

1004
01:52:39,400 --> 01:52:42,390
Always some excuse.
And if possible something big.

1005
01:52:43,100 --> 01:52:45,930
Sorry Lilly. I'm too old for that joke.

1006
01:52:46,960 --> 01:52:50,590
You betrayed yourself.
You and no one else.

1007
01:52:53,370 --> 01:52:54,670
I loved her so much Ilse.

1008
01:52:57,270 --> 01:52:59,900
I did too.
- But not like I did.

1009
01:53:02,700 --> 01:53:04,430
If it makes you happy...

1010
01:53:07,040 --> 01:53:12,710
Were you really together with that many?
- Oh yes. I liked quite a few.

1011
01:53:14,280 --> 01:53:18,380
People are so different Lilly.
With luck something might remain.

1012
01:53:18,750 --> 01:53:21,110
It was surely more platonic.
- Oh no.

1013
01:53:21,640 --> 01:53:23,340
I'm definitely a little pig.

1014
01:53:24,950 --> 01:53:27,180
But that doesn't matter.

1015
01:53:42,390 --> 01:53:44,080
50 years Ilse.

1016
01:53:47,360 --> 01:53:48,450
50 years.

1017
01:53:52,070 --> 01:53:53,460
And one thought.

1018
01:53:56,160 --> 01:53:57,320
One face.

1019
01:54:00,130 --> 01:54:00,990
One name.

1020
01:54:01,360 --> 01:54:05,990
Sweetheart one is a stupid number.
It's never enough. That's the problem.

1021
01:54:07,240 --> 01:54:10,600
Come back to the house! Lunch is ready!

1022
01:54:11,540 --> 01:54:14,690
Was it my fault Ilse?

1023
01:54:16,640 --> 01:54:22,370
I don't know Lilly.
I was always certain. Too certain.

1024
01:54:24,280 --> 01:54:26,640
Felice stayed because she loved you.

1025
01:54:27,180 --> 01:54:29,640
And you went to see her because you loved her.

1026
01:54:31,540 --> 01:54:33,370
I can't tell you anything more.

1027
01:54:34,010 --> 01:54:36,670
Hello ladies. We're waiting for you.

1028
01:54:38,010 --> 01:54:43,680
Sure dearie. You haven't got
the slightest idea. Come on Lilly.

1029
01:54:49,350 --> 01:54:52,340
"A love that lasts forever. "
Know what Felice said?

1030
01:54:52,720 --> 01:54:55,550
"That greedy Mrs. Wust
just can't get enough.

1031
01:54:56,090 --> 01:55:01,580
She made me sign a contract:
'Forever. ' Sounds like a gravestone. "

1032
01:55:02,400 --> 01:55:06,620
No she didn't say "like a gravestone. "
- Yes she did.

1033
01:55:09,260 --> 01:55:10,490
Come on Lilly.

1034
01:55:39,050 --> 01:55:42,990
This moves the film
and this is how you focus.

1035
01:55:44,270 --> 01:55:49,270
Lovely cards. Who are they from?
- Capt. Ernst Biermösl. God bless him.

1036
01:56:02,350 --> 01:56:06,650
Did you notice I changed the key?
- I didn't notice you'd even found one.

1037
01:56:07,190 --> 01:56:12,720
Isn't that awful?... "Forever and ever"
sounds like an epitaph.

1038
01:56:13,260 --> 01:56:16,550
I thought it was nice.
- What about you mouse? What d'you say?

1039
01:56:17,090 --> 01:56:21,080
About what?
- The one and only true ideal love.

1040
01:56:21,460 --> 01:56:26,120
You can look for it. - Horrible.
One love and you have to look for it!

1041
01:56:26,500 --> 01:56:28,460
Leave her alone now.

1042
01:56:28,830 --> 01:56:31,460
Life is not like that.
It scratches and scrapes...

1043
01:56:31,830 --> 01:56:34,730
...and all at once you clean the windows.
- Not me.

1044
01:56:35,260 --> 01:56:37,390
Listen to that. Real romantic.

1045
01:56:37,760 --> 01:56:42,360
"Falling in love again
never wanted to.

1046
01:56:42,800 --> 01:56:45,130
What is she to do?"

1047
01:56:45,510 --> 01:56:47,370
And you?
- "She can't help it. "

1048
01:56:47,740 --> 01:56:52,500
What do you want Felice?
- Me?... You all of you everyone.

1049
01:56:53,040 --> 01:56:56,660
Everything! But I'd be satisfied
with one single moment...

1050
01:56:57,210 --> 01:57:00,470
...so perfect it would last a lifetime.
- That's easy.

1051
01:57:00,840 --> 01:57:05,080
Where do you find something like that?
- For example this one here is great.

1052
01:57:06,480 --> 01:57:09,000
I don't want "forever. " I want "now!"

1053
01:57:09,380 --> 01:57:12,240
Now! Now! Now!

1054
01:57:13,610 --> 01:57:16,710
I want loads of "nows!" And I want them
till I turn old and gray.

1055
01:57:17,650 --> 01:57:20,180
And besides I want more cake.

1056
01:57:22,460 --> 01:57:23,580
Again.

1057
01:57:29,690 --> 01:57:32,590
After the war Lilly waited in vain
for Felice for many years.

1058
01:57:33,120 --> 01:57:35,650
The exact circumstances
of Felice's death are unknown.

1059
01:57:36,190 --> 01:57:38,660
She probably died during
one of the notorius death marches.

1060
01:57:41,060 --> 01:57:48,620
Today in the spring of 1999
84-year-old Lilly Wust lives in Berlin.

